metadata.name: Refractions #284
metadata.description:
Refractions is a study of frequencies, harmonies and abstract representations of natural phenomena. 

It is an experiment of blending three colors to create integrated textural compositions.


Probabilities;

- 14 compositions with variations.

- 2 background color.

- 19 different base color palette (2 monochrome).

- 2 distinct textures with variations.

-  2 different alpha types; tangential & sinusoidal.

- Different edges.

- Several starting positions and styles (wavy or straight).


Made with p5.js

Ilgın İçözü, April 2022
@distcollective

metadata.name: Suspension #32
metadata.description:
Suspension uses simple objects to create structures suspended in space, held together by relation and composition.

The unique composition algorithm is random enough to produce infinite variations, but ordered enough to produce engaging artworks that are instantly recognizable.

Suspension uses negative space, additive coloring, and a unique rendering technique to create a very distinct style. 

It has many hand tuned palettes, with rare palettes that produce incisive variations.

Suspension is responsive and will render fast at any resolution. It looks great on wide screens of 2K, 4K or larger.

To accommodate the variation in displays, you can use the up/down arrow keys to adjust the brightness. 'r' resets to the default values.

's' will save an image in the exact size of the window, so you can create images in any resolution.

metadata.name: Acid Quilt #385
metadata.description:
This is an abstract work. There is no true or correct orientation.

Inspired by repeater patterns, tiles, tessellations, and quilts. Not as goofy as the Collage of Collage set but still some goofiness to it. This collage set is made up of layers sketched on a really old ipad. 

The project does not have a repeater functions built in, just produces the single base unit. My hope is that the output be used on a larger canvas and repeated, tiled, or tessellated. Some outputs might could look good in a quilt. 

These online tools (as of Feb 2022) are easy to use for making tiles. Windows also makes it easy to tile, as does Photoshop:
- https://www.imgonline.com.ua/eng/check-texture-tiling.php
- https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/windows/win32/gdiplus/-gdiplus-tiling-a-shape-with-an-image-use
- https://prinfab.com/printed-fabric?r2=magic

(^This^ is very much not a best practice, including links in this description that might not exist in the future)

There are more than 1.3 billion possible combos!

Please enjoy!

metadata.name: Euphonic #1004
metadata.description:
Euphonic is an exploration of the emergent visual properties that arise from placing layers of simple lines atop one another.

In general this effect is called the Moiré effect. This effect really feels best in the tactile - when you have a printed page and an acetate sheet. This piece attempts to recreate that tactile joy.

This is built in WebGL 2 and so doesn't work in Safari 14 and below. All latest browsers will work as expected.

Licensing: BY-NC-ND see license.md for details.
